org.sbolstandard.core

Interface Collection

  • All Superinterfaces:
    SBOLNamedObject, SBOLObject, SBOLRootObject, SBOLVisitable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CollectionImpl
    Deprecated.

    @Deprecated
public interface Collection
extends SBOLNamedObject, SBOLRootObject
    The SBOL data model's Collection for RDF and Json. The objects of this type represent an organizational container which helps users and developers conceptualize a set of DNA components and SequenceFeatures as a group. Any combination of these objects can be added to a Collection, annotated with a displayID, name and description and be shared on the web. Such collections could be a set of restriction enzyme recognition sites, such as the features commonly used for BBF RFC 10 BioBricks. A Collection could contain all the DNA components used in a specific project, lab, or any custom grouping specified by the user.
